<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pholyotha &amp; Sutcharit &amp; Lin &amp; Panha" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Benson" baseAuthorityYear="1859" family="Helicarionidae" genus="Burmochlamys" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Burmochlamys perpaula" order="Eupulmonata" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="perpaula">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Burmochlamys perpaula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is currently known only from the type locality in Tenasserim Valley (
<bibRefCitation author="Benson, WH" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B2" refString="Benson, WH, 1859. New Helicidae collected by W. Theobald, Esq., jun., in Burmah and the Khasia Hills, and described by W.H. Benson. Annals and Magazine of Natural History series 3 3: 387-393." title="New Helicidae collected by W. Theobald, Esq., jun., in Burmah and the Khasia Hills, and described by W. H. Benson. Annals and Magazine of Natural History series 3 3: 387 - 393." year="1859">Benson 1859</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.13103" author="Blanford, WT" journalOrPublisher="Taylor and Francis, London" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B3" refString="Blanford, WT, Godwin-Austen, HH, 1908. The Fauna of British India, including Ceylon and Burma. Mollusca. Testacellidae and Zonitidae. Taylor and Francis, London, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.13103" title="The Fauna of British India, including Ceylon and Burma. Mollusca. Testacellidae and Zonitidae." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.13103" year="1908">Blanford and Godwin-Austen 1908</bibRefCitation>
). The original type series could not be located, and no specimens were found in this study. Therefore, the generic placement is still provisional and awaiting for further anatomical information. However, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pholyotha &amp; Sutcharit &amp; Lin &amp; Panha" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Pholyotha &amp; Sutcharit &amp; Lin &amp; Panha" baseAuthorityYear="2022" class="Gastropoda" family="Helicarionidae" genus="Helix" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Helix perpaula" order="Eupulmonata" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="perpaula">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Helix perpaula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is transferred to this new genus, which it distinct from the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1847" class="Gastropoda" family="Helicarionidae" genus="Macrochlamys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Macrochlamys" order="Eupulmonata" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Macrochlamys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by a numbers of shell morphology (see 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1080/13235818.2020.1723041" author="Pholyotha, A" journalOrPublisher="Molluscan Research" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="183 - 204" refId="B24" refString="Pholyotha, A, Sutcharit, C, Tongkerd, P, Lin, A, Panha, S, 2020b. Taxonomic revision of the land snail genera Macrochlamys Gray, 1847 and Sarika Godwin-Austen, 1907 (Eupulmonata: Ariophantidae) from Southeastern Myanmar, with descriptions of three new species. Molluscan Research 40 (2): 183 - 204, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1080/13235818.2020.1723041" title="Taxonomic revision of the land snail genera Macrochlamys Gray, 1847 and Sarika Godwin-Austen, 1907 (Eupulmonata: Ariophantidae) from Southeastern Myanmar, with descriptions of three new species." url="https://doi.org/10.1080/13235818.2020.1723041" volume="40" year="2020 b">Pholyotha et al. 2020b</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pholyotha &amp; Sutcharit &amp; Lin &amp; Panha" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Benson" baseAuthorityYear="1859" family="Helicarionidae" genus="Burmochlamys" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Burmochlamys perpaula" order="Eupulmonata" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="perpaula">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Burmochlamys perpaula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterised by subglobose, small size (width of ~ 2.0 mm, height of ~ 1.3 mm), obliquely striated and very minutely spirally ribbed throughout, moderately elevated spire, rather more convex body whorl, and narrowly crescent-shaped aperture, simple peristome, simple columellar margin with slightly reflected near umbilicus, and narrowly open umbilicus (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Shells of Burmochlamys species A, B B. cassidula specimen CUMZ 14209 C B. cauisa specimen NHMUK 1888.12.4.465 - 466 D B. perpaula specimen NHMUK 1903.7.1.533 E, F B. poongee E specimen NHMUK 1888.12.4.23 - 6 F specimen CUMZ 14210." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1110.82461.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/709572" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">6D</figureCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Benson, WH" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B2" refString="Benson, WH, 1859. New Helicidae collected by W. Theobald, Esq., jun., in Burmah and the Khasia Hills, and described by W.H. Benson. Annals and Magazine of Natural History series 3 3: 387-393." title="New Helicidae collected by W. Theobald, Esq., jun., in Burmah and the Khasia Hills, and described by W. H. Benson. Annals and Magazine of Natural History series 3 3: 387 - 393." year="1859">Benson 1859</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.13103" author="Blanford, WT" journalOrPublisher="Taylor and Francis, London" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B3" refString="Blanford, WT, Godwin-Austen, HH, 1908. The Fauna of British India, including Ceylon and Burma. Mollusca. Testacellidae and Zonitidae. Taylor and Francis, London, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.13103" title="The Fauna of British India, including Ceylon and Burma. Mollusca. Testacellidae and Zonitidae." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.13103" year="1908">Blanford and Godwin-Austen 1908</bibRefCitation>
). In addition, this species can be distinguished from all other congeners by its moderately elevated spire, rather more convex body whorl, and narrower umbilicus. In comparison, most species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pholyotha &amp; Panha" authorityYear="2022" family="Helicarionidae" genus="Burmochlamys" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Burmochlamys" order="Eupulmonata" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Burmochlamys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
gen. nov. have a higher shell spire, rather broad and well-rounded last whorl, and relatively wider umbilicus.
</paragraph>
